<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf3d6fb27-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc" identifier="/us/usc/t35/s281"><num value="281">§ 281.</num><heading> Remedy for infringement of patent</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A patentee shall have remedy by civil action for infringement of his patent.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf3d6fb28-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">(<ref href="/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950">July 19, 1952, ch. 950</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/66/812">66 Stat. 812</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf3d6fb29-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idf3d6fb2a-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., §§ 67 and 70, part (R.S. 4919; R.S. 4921, amended (1) <ref href="/us/act/1897-03-03/ch391/s6">Mar. 3, 1897, ch. 391, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/29/694">29 Stat. 694</ref>, (2) <ref href="/us/act/1922-02-18/ch58/s8">Feb. 18, 1922, ch. 58, § 8</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/392">42 Stat. 392</ref>, (3) <ref href="/us/act/1946-08-01/ch726/s1">Aug. 1, 1946, ch. 726, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/60/778">60 Stat. 778</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The corresponding two sections of existing law are divided among sections 281, 283, 284, 285, 286 and 289 with some changes in language. Section 281 serves as an introduction or preamble to the following sections, the modern term civil action is used, there would be, of course, a right to a jury trial when no injunction is sought.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
